          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1643122848522-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1643122848522-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1643122848522-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and chop the<strong> red onions</strong> into wedges</p><p>Crush the <strong>garlic</strong> with the side of a knife, keeping the skins on</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643122868031-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643122868031-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643122868031-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643122868031-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643122868031-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>red onion wedges</strong> and <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> to a large roasting tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and<strong> yellow mustard seeds</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
      "order": 3,
